  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p>This is a short blogpost documenting the steps I took to get APA 7 running in <code>papaja</code> for Rmarkdown. I followed more detailed instructions in the blogpost <a href="https://www.martinasladek.co.uk/content/blog/2022_feb_how-to-set-up-papaja-to-work-with-apa-7-format.html">How to set up {papaja} to work with the APA 7 format</a>, and also took a look at an <a href="https://github.com/crsh/papaja/issues/342">open issue on the <code>papaja</code> GitHub repo</a> on this topic.</p>
<section id="setting-up-apa-7-in-papaja" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="setting-up-apa-7-in-papaja">Setting up APA 7 in <code>papaja</code></h2>
<p><a href="https://github.com/crsh/papaja"><code>papaja</code></a> is an R package for preparing APA-styled articles in Rmarkdown. Itâ€™s current version (0.1.2) supports APA 6 guidelines, although the newest guidelines are APA 7. Basically, we need to get <code>papaja</code> to use APA 7.</p>
<p>I achieved this by following these steps:</p>
<ol type="1">
<li>Install developer version of <code>papaja</code>:</li>
</ol>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb1" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb1-1">remotes<span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">::</span><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">install_github</span>(<span class="st" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">"crsh/papaja@devel"</span>)</span></code></pre></div>
</div>
<ol start="2" type="1">
<li>Add to the YAML:</li>
</ol>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb2" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb2-1"><span class="an" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">csl               :</span><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;"> "`r system.file('rmd', 'apa7.csl', package = 'papaja')`"</span></span>
<span id="cb2-2"><span class="an" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">documentclass     :</span><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;"> "apa7"</span></span></code></pre></div>
</div>
<p>And this:</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb3" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb3-1"><span class="an" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">header-includes:</span></span>
<span id="cb3-2"><span class="ss" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">  - </span>|</span>
<span id="cb3-3">    \makeatletter</span>
<span id="cb3-4">    \renewcommand{\paragraph}{\@startsection{paragraph}{4}{\parindent}%</span>
<span id="cb3-5">      {0\baselineskip \@plus 0.2ex \@minus 0.2ex}%</span>
<span id="cb3-6">      {-1em}%</span>
<span id="cb3-7">      {\normalfont\normalsize\bfseries\typesectitle}}</span>
<span id="cb3-8">    </span>
<span id="cb3-9">    \renewcommand{\subparagraph}<span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">[</span><span class="ot" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">1</span><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">]</span>{\@startsection{subparagraph}{5}{1em}%</span>
<span id="cb3-10">      {0\baselineskip \@plus 0.2ex \@minus 0.2ex}%</span>
<span id="cb3-11">      {-\z@\relax}%</span>
<span id="cb3-12">      {\normalfont\normalsize\bfseries\itshape\hspace{\parindent}{#1}\textit{\addperi}}{\relax}}</span>
<span id="cb3-13">    \makeatother</span></code></pre></div>
</div>
<p>This was sufficient for my set-up. The additional LaTeX packages I needed were then listed directly under (and in line with) <code>\makatother</code>.</p>
</section>
<section id="testing" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="testing">Testing</h2>
<p>To test if APA 7 vs.&nbsp;6 was being used, I changed a BibTex entry for a reference to have more than 7 authors (e.g., by repeating all the author names until &gt;7). I then changed <code>csl: "</code>/Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/4.3-arm64/Resources/library/papaja/rmd/apa7.csl<code>"</code> to <code>csl: "</code>/Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/4.3-arm64/Resources/library/papaja/rmd/apa6.csl<code>"</code>. In the bibliography only 7 authors were listed (following apa 6). I then changed it back to <code>'apa7.csl</code>, and the rendered bibliography listed all authors (following apa 7). I took this as sufficient evidence that apa 7 was indeed being used. I then changed the BibTex authors back, of course.</p>
</section>
